  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (v0.5 synthetic)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The hemolysis accumulation model relies on the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law damage integral, whose derivation assumes a linear superposition of instantaneous shear-stress exposures (i.e., damage contributions are IID and additive across Lagrangian fluid parcels). The assessment narrative states this linearity assumption is 'broadly applicable to rotary blood pumps' without providing a validation result that tests whether the assumption holds under the turbulent, recirculating flow regimes characteristic of the CPB operating envelope described in the COU.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-cfd-identifies-worstcase-hemolysis",
