      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match COU operating envelope within ±10%.",
      "rationale": "PIV and bench tests conducted at 5 L/min and 3000 RPM with 40% glycerol blood analog (viscosity 3.5 mPa·s). COU operating range spans 3–6 L/min and 2500–3500 RPM. All test conditions fall within ±8% of COU nominal values. Criterion met."
